{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3348807,"name":"Sofie Budman","username":"sofieb15","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/f08c70/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-01T02:54:23.856Z","cooked":"<p>Hi everyone. We are trying to put LEDs on our robot this year, but have been having issues. When we run the code on our previous years robot, it works perfectly, but when we try it on the practice board or this years robot with the same wiring, random lights turn on and there is no control over  which ones they are and which color. Any advice?</p>
<p>here is the code</p>
<p>public Led(IntakeShooter intakeShooter) {<br>
this.intakeshooter = intakeShooter;<br>
led.setLength(ledBuffer.getLength());<br>
led.setData(ledBuffer);<br>
led.start();</p>
